        { slug "george-orwell-and-effective-coding" </ url derived /> date @2011-10-26T00:00:00@ updated @2011-10-26T00:00:00@ excerpt "Earlier today I read an essay on the decline of the English language by George Orwell. The essay is excellent, and I'm already trying to apply its lessons to my writing, but there was one passage that struck me as being particularly useful for software development." order 18 }
        { slug "compute-magazine-archives" </ url derived /> date @2011-05-15T00:00:00@ updated @2011-05-15T00:00:00@ excerpt "I just found an archive of COMPUTE! magazine, which is the magazine that taught me how to program in the 1980's. Just recently I was lamenting not keeping every single issue I ever had (which was most of them), but now I can flip back through them any time. Looking through the site really brought back some memories of when I first started messing with computers, around 1983 or so." order 19 }
